Comment_contributor: In counting eta is used, not tai.
The Prefix e, no doubt verbal, can be used with all but tanahuru [<taŋahuru>, with <n> in italics].
To all Cardinals, except tanahuru [<taŋahuru>, with <n> in italics], ta is sometimes prefixed
[<tanahuru>, with <n> in italics]; For the sum above ten madara is used by some.
A score, used in counting betel nuts and days, is gagau ... but it is not admitted that this word is kakau fingers.
